Helmed by Farhan Akhtar , ' Don : The Chase Begins Again' starred Shah Rukh Khan Kareena Kapoor Khan , Arjun Rampal, Boman Irani, Isha Koppikar among others. The film was released on 20 October 2006. It completed 14 years today.On this special day, Farhan took to his Twitter handle to pen a special note. He tweeted, ''Don ko yaad rakhne ki zaroorat nahin kyon ki Don ko bhool jaana namumkin hai. #14YearsOfDon''.Producer Ritesh Sidhwani wrote, ''It's #14YearsOfDon already, and I can still remember every day of shoot so vividly. What beautiful memories! A big virtual hug and lots of love & light to a kickass team who made this movie etched in ours and audiences' hearts forever''.Check out their tweets here:Speaking about the movie, it is a remake of the 1978 film of the same name. A sequel , which was also directed by Farhan, and released in 2011.As soon as they shared the post, fans reacted to Farhan’s post by demanding the long-awaited ' Don 3 '.Check out their reactions here:Meanwhile, on the work front, SRK was last seen in Aanand L Rai's 'Zero' starring Katrina Kaif and Anushka Sharma.
